# Testing Conventions — 1BT WIKI

## Testing Pyramid
```
         [Cypress E2E]         ← few, high-value user journeys
       [Integration Tests]     ← API endpoint + DB (use test DB)
     [Unit Tests (Services)]   ← business logic, mocked dependencies
```

## Unit Tests — Jest

### What to test
- **Every service method** must have a corresponding unit test
- Focus on: state transitions, validation rules, error cases, business logic
- Mock: repositories, external APIs (Claude, Clerk), notification senders

### File naming
- Unit test: `src/services/__tests__/article.service.test.ts`
- Or co-located: `src/services/article.service.test.ts`

### Test structure (AAA pattern)
```typescript
// src/services/__tests__/article.service.test.ts
import { ArticleService } from '../article.service';
import { articleRepository } from '../../repositories/article.repository';
import { AppError } from '../../errors/AppError';

jest.mock('../../repositories/article.repository');
const mockRepo = articleRepository as jest.Mocked<typeof articleRepository>;

describe('ArticleService', () => {
  let service: ArticleService;

  beforeEach(() => {
    service = new ArticleService();
    jest.clearAllMocks();
  });

  describe('submitForReview', () => {
    it('should transition Draft article to Pending', async () => {
      // Arrange
      const draftArticle = { id: 'abc', status: 'Draft', authorId: 'user-1' };
      mockRepo.findById.mockResolvedValue(draftArticle);
      mockRepo.updateStatus.mockResolvedValue({ ...draftArticle, status: 'Pending' });

      // Act
      const result = await service.submitForReview('abc', 'user-1');

      // Assert
      expect(result.status).toBe('Pending');
      expect(mockRepo.updateStatus).toHaveBeenCalledWith('abc', 'Pending');
    });

    it('should throw AppError when article is not in Draft status', async () => {
      mockRepo.findById.mockResolvedValue({ id: 'abc', status: 'Published', authorId: 'user-1' });

      await expect(service.submitForReview('abc', 'user-1'))
        .rejects.toThrow(new AppError('Only Draft articles can be submitted', 400));
    });

    it('should throw AppError when user is not the article author', async () => {
      mockRepo.findById.mockResolvedValue({ id: 'abc', status: 'Draft', authorId: 'other-user' });

      await expect(service.submitForReview('abc', 'user-1'))
        .rejects.toThrow(new AppError('Not authorized', 403));
    });
  });
});
```

### Required unit tests per owner

**Lahiru** must cover:
- `AuthService`: Google OAuth callback, domain restriction, deactivated account check
- `SessionService`: JWT issue, validate, revoke
- `CommentService`: create, edit own, delete own, block edit of others
- `LikeService`: like (idempotent), unlike, count aggregation
- `QuizService`: generate (Published only check), evaluate scoring, empty submission block

**Chathurika** must cover:
- `UserService`: role assignment (Admin only), activate/deactivate
- `ProfileService`: view/update own profile
- `ReviewService`: approve (Pending → Published), reject + feedback, notification triggers
- `NotificationService`: persist, list, mark read, unread count
- `TechTalkService`: create, publish, edit (resets to Draft), republish, delete

**Malindu** must cover:
- `ArticleService`: create, edit draft, submit, list published, list own, soft delete
- `AdminDashboardService`: aggregate stats (users, articles, pending reviews, tech talks)

## Integration Tests

### Scope
- Test full HTTP request → controller → service → repository → test DB
- Use a separate test database (configure via `DATABASE_URL_TEST` env var)
- Seed test DB before each suite; clean up after

### Pattern
```typescript
// src/__tests__/integration/articles.integration.test.ts
import request from 'supertest';
import { app } from '../../app';
import { seedTestUser, seedTestArticle, cleanDb } from '../helpers/db.helpers';

describe('Article Lifecycle Integration', () => {
  let authorToken: string;
  let reviewerToken: string;

  beforeAll(async () => {
    await cleanDb();
    authorToken = await seedTestUser({ role: 'User' });
    reviewerToken = await seedTestUser({ role: 'Reviewer' });
  });

  afterAll(async () => {
    await cleanDb();
  });

  it('should complete full lifecycle: Draft → Pending → Published', async () => {
    // Create article
    const createRes = await request(app)
      .post('/api/v1/articles')
      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${authorToken}`)
      .send({ title: 'Test Article', body: {}, tags: ['test'] })
      .expect(201);

    const articleId = createRes.body.data.id;
    expect(createRes.body.data.status).toBe('Draft');

    // Submit for review
    await request(app)
      .post(`/api/v1/articles/${articleId}/submit`)
      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${authorToken}`)
      .expect(200);

    // Reviewer approves
    const approveRes = await request(app)
      .patch(`/api/v1/reviewer/articles/${articleId}/approve`)
      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${reviewerToken}`)
      .expect(200);

    expect(approveRes.body.data.status).toBe('Published');
  });
});
```

## Cypress E2E Tests

### What to cover (per MVP)
- **MVP 1**: Login with Google → protected route access → logout
- **MVP 2**: Create article → submit → reviewer approves → visible on homepage
- **MVP 3**: View article → generate quiz → answer → submit → view score
- **MVP 4**: Admin dashboard → assign role → deactivate user → verify lockout

### File naming and location
```
cypress/
  e2e/
    mvp1-auth.cy.ts
    mvp2-article-lifecycle.cy.ts
    mvp3-quiz.cy.ts
    mvp4-admin.cy.ts
  support/
    commands.ts         ← custom commands: cy.login(), cy.createArticle()
    e2e.ts
  fixtures/
    test-user.json
    test-article.json
```

### Custom command pattern
```typescript
// cypress/support/commands.ts
Cypress.Commands.add('login', (role: 'User' | 'Reviewer' | 'Admin' = 'User') => {
  cy.session([role], () => {
    cy.visit('/login');
    // Mock Clerk auth for testing
    cy.window().then((win) => {
      win.localStorage.setItem('__test_role', role);
    });
  });
});

Cypress.Commands.add('createArticle', (title: string, tags: string[]) => {
  cy.visit('/articles/create');
  cy.get('[data-testid="article-title"]').type(title);
  cy.get('[data-testid="tiptap-editor"]').type('Article content');
  cy.get('[data-testid="save-draft-btn"]').click();
});
```

### Data attributes (use these in components for Cypress targeting)
Always add `data-testid` to interactive elements:
```tsx
<button data-testid="submit-article-btn">Submit for Review</button>
<input data-testid="article-title-input" />
<div data-testid="article-status-badge">{status}</div>
<button data-testid="confirm-modal-btn">Confirm</button>
```

## Coverage Targets
| Type | Target |
|------|--------|
| Unit (Service layer) | ≥ 80% |
| Integration (API routes) | Key happy paths + main error cases |
| Cypress E2E | 1 happy path per MVP feature |

## SonarQube Quality Gate
- No new bugs or vulnerabilities
- Code coverage report uploaded after each CI run
- Duplications < 3%
- All `// TODO` or `// FIXME` comments must be tracked as issues
